# Next.js Frontend Rules

## Deployment Target
- This app deploys to Cloudflare Workers via `@opennextjs/cloudflare`
- Do NOT use `next/image` default loader — it requires Node.js sharp. Use Cloudflare Images or a simple `<img>` tag
- Do NOT use `next export` — OpenNext handles the build
- Compatibility date must be `2025-04-01` or later in wrangler.jsonc (required for `process.env` population)
- Enable `nodejs_compat` flag in wrangler.jsonc

## App Router Patterns
- Use Server Components by default — only add `'use client'` when interactivity is required
- Never call Supabase directly from client components — use Server Actions or Route Handlers
- Supabase service_role key is NEVER passed to client components or browser
- Use `cookies()` from `next/headers` in Server Components for Supabase session
- Route Handlers (`app/api/**/route.ts`) handle webhooks; Workers handle the scan engine

## Supabase Client Pattern
```typescript
// lib/supabase/server.ts — for Server Components and Server Actions
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr';
import { cookies } from 'next/headers';

export function createClient() {
  const cookieStore = cookies();
  return createServerClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!, // anon key only — never service_role here
    { cookies: { getAll: () => cookieStore.getAll(), setAll: (cs) => cs.forEach(({ name, value, options }) => cookieStore.set(name, value, options)) } }
  );
}
```

## Forms and Mutations
- Use Server Actions for all form submissions
- Validate all inputs server-side — never trust client-side validation alone
- Use `zod` for schema validation on all form inputs
- Return structured errors from Server Actions, never throw unhandled exceptions to the client

## Score Display
- The score badge must be visible BEFORE the email gate — users see the number first, then are asked for email
- Score name: always "AI Search Readiness Score" — never any other phrasing
- Letter grades: A+ (90-100), B (75-89), C (55-74), D (35-54), F (0-34)
- Design intent: most sites should visually land in the 45-65 range (C grade triggers action)

## Social Share / OG Images
- Generate OG images using `next/og` (ImageResponse) in a Route Handler
- OG image must include: score badge, letter grade, domain name, benchmark percentile
- Pre-populate share copy: `"My site scored {score}/100 on GEO readiness 🤖 Check yours → geopulse.io"`
- Add competitive framing: "You scored better than {percentile}% of sites in your industry"

## Authentication
- Use Supabase Auth magic link + Google OAuth — do NOT write custom auth
- Auth state lives in Supabase session cookies, not localStorage
- Protected routes: use middleware.ts with `@supabase/ssr` to check session
- After $29 purchase: auto-create account via magic link email (user did not sign up separately)

## Cloudflare Turnstile
- Embed Turnstile widget on the scan form using the official `@marsidev/react-turnstile` package
- Pass the token to the scan API — never skip this check
- Use invisible challenge mode for lowest friction

## UI Constraints
- Dark-mode-adjacent visual design — score-centric, minimal
- Mobile-first: scan form must be fully functional on mobile
- Results page must load and display score in <8 seconds end-to-end
- Email gate appears after score is visible — not before

## What Stitch-Generated Components Should Follow
- When importing components from Stitch, wrap them to match these naming and type conventions
- Ensure all Stitch components are typed — add TypeScript interfaces for props
- Never use inline styles from Stitch output — convert to Tailwind utility classes
- Check Stitch-generated components for hardcoded colours that should use CSS variables
